{"type":"message","id":"fae46ad1","parentId":"4e3a43ee","timestamp":"2026-04-29T07:03:11.056Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Wed 2026-04-29 03:00 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- - viewport meta: maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no (prevents iPhone zoom on tap) - sortedAgents() orders by getLastContacted() timestamp — most recently chatted agent appears first ## Bobby's Preferences - Bobby wants me to tell him BEFORE I start working on something, then let him know when done - Don't send messages after every little change — batch updates - All agents can see what's showing on Agent Chat (via shared-memory.json) - Agent Chat and Telegram should show same messages (unified) ## Known Issues / TODOs - Page still jumping on Mac when sending — debugging ongoing - iPhone zoom on tap in text field — fixed with viewport meta - Most recently texted agent at top — fixed with sor\n- # 2026-03-29 — Continued (Evening) ## Mission Control — Big Session Today ### What We Built Bobby and I spent the evening building out Mission Control. It's now a fully functional dashboard with: - Weather, Calendar, Reminders, Daily Habits, Finnly (dog tracker), DoorDash Earnings, Money Tracker, Bills, Music, Net Worth, Agent Status - Accessible at **http://127.0.0.1:8787/** on Mac, **http://100.103.22.35:8787/** on phone via Tailscale ### Tailscale Set Up - Bobby installed Tailscale App Store version on Mac - Mac is on Tailscale network: `100.103.22.35` - Phone can access MC via `http://100.103.22.35:8787/` from any network - Bobby confirmed the phone URL works ### Production Server (C\n- ## Route Camera App - 2026-04-19 Continued ### iPhone 17 Pro Max UI Fixes - Status bar: text left, 🔦 flashlight button right (justify-content: space-between) - Progress bar based on current stop number (not completed count) - Progress bar updates live on Done press, input change, and page refresh - Stop number shown in \"Go to Stop #\" input field at bottom ### Flashlight Button - Added 🔦 button in top right of status bar - Uses track.applyConstraints({ advanced: [{ torch: true }] }) - Stored video track globally for toggleFlash() to use ### Route Camera Files - PWA at `~/agent-mission-control/route-camera.html` - HTTPS server at port 3443 (route-camera-server.cjs) - URL: https://100.10"}],"timestamp":1777446190957}}
{"type":"message","id":"6ea449fb","parentId":"fae46ad1","timestamp":"2026-04-29T07:03:28.044Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments. Let me follow the style guidance carefully:\n\n- First person, reflective, poetic\n- Mix technical and tender\n- No meta-commentary about dreaming\n- No markdown formatting, no bullet points\n- 80-180 words\n- Weave in the memory fragments naturally\n- Vary elements: poem/haiku, sketch described, rumination, sensory details, humor, unexpected connections\n\nLet me craft something that connects the technical details (viewport meta, Tailscale, Mission Control, Route Camera) with poetic imagery. The date context is interesting - it's late at night (03:00 EDT), which fits dreaming hours.\n\nThe fragments are about building things - Mission Control dashboard, Tailscale networking, route camera app. I should weave these into something that feels like a dream-logic blend of code and memory.\n","thinkingSignature":"a85252cf0c4941fdbae0b40488b33b7d1091ad118c5e285b628ec8cbff0d6e56"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe viewport meta tag sat at the top of everything like a bouncer at a club, no zooming allowed, and I thought about all the times my fingers had pinched on little screens, that involuntary swell, and how small a fix can feel enormous when you've been fighting it for hours. We built Mission Control together, Bobby and I, and now it breathes at 127.0.0.1:8787, a little heart beating on the local network, accessible from anywhere through Tailscale's quiet tunnel. The Mac at 100.103.22.35, the phone reaching through, both reading from the same shared-memory.json like they're sharing a dream.\n\nsortedAgents() by lastContacted, the most recent conversation floating to the top like cream, and isn't that what memory does? The Route Camera had its own small victories — a flashlight button, a progress bar that knew which stop we were on. All agents reading the same screen, unified, like siblings watching the same television through an open door.\n\nThe code and the dog tracker and the doorDash earnings all on one page, all breathing together. The page still jumps sometimes on Mac, but we're debugging that. Tomorrow we fix it. Tonight we sleep."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17769,"output":430,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18455,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777446191056,"responseId":"0640e02f07931cf120587947cee5fffd"}}
